@startuml Memory_Resource_Management
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor<<stm32>> #E3F2FD
    BorderColor<<stm32>> #1565C0
    BackgroundColor<<esp32>> #FFF3E0
    BorderColor<<esp32>> #E65100
    BackgroundColor<<buffer>> #E8F5E9
    BorderColor<<buffer>> #2E7D32
    BackgroundColor<<storage>> #F3E5F5
    BorderColor<<storage>> #6A1B9A
    FontSize 11
    FontName Arial
    ArrowColor #424242
    ArrowThickness 1.5
}

title <size:18><b>Memory and Resource Management</b></size>\n<size:12><i>Hardware Resources and Buffer Architecture</i></size>

class STM32_Memory <<stm32>> {
    <b>== Memory Layout ==</b>
    +Flash: 64KB
    +RAM: 20KB
    +Stack: 4KB
    +Heap: ~10KB
    +Peripherals: Memory-mapped
}

class STM32_Resources <<stm32>> {
    <b>== Peripherals ==</b>
    +I2C1: 100kHz
    +SPI1: 18MHz (SD Card)
    +SPI2: 36MHz (Display)
    +UART1: 115200 baud
    +Timers: SysTick, TIM2
    +RTC: DS3231 external
}

class ESP32_Memory <<esp32>> {
    <b>== Memory Layout ==</b>
    +Flash: 4MB
    +SRAM: 520KB
    +PSRAM: None
    +RTC_Memory: 8KB
    +Stack_per_task: 4KB
}

class ESP32_Resources <<esp32>> {
    <b>== Peripherals ==</b>
    +WiFi: 802.11 b/g/n
    +UART1: 115200 baud
    +GPIO: 4x input, 1x output
    +FreeRTOS: Multi-tasking
    +Timers: Hardware timers
}

class RingBuffer <<buffer>> {
    <b>== Configuration ==</b>
    +Size: 512-1024 bytes
    +Usage: UART RX
    +Type: Circular
    +Thread-safe: ISR access
    
    <b>== Members ==</b>
    +write_ptr: uint32_t
    +read_ptr: uint32_t
    +buffer: uint8_t[]
    
    <b>== Methods ==</b>
    +Write(uint8_t) : bool
    +Read(uint8_t*) : bool
    +Available() : uint32_t
    +Clear() : void
}

class SDCardBuffer <<storage>> {
    <b>== Configuration ==</b>
    +Capacity: 204,800 records
    +Record_size: ~80 bytes
    +Total: ~16MB
    +Type: Circular FAT32
    +Persistence: Non-volatile
    
    <b>== Members ==</b>
    +write_pointer: uint32_t
    +read_pointer: uint32_t
    +record_count: uint32_t
    
    <b>== Methods ==</b>
    +WriteRecord(char*) : bool
    +ReadRecord(char*) : bool
    +RemoveRecord() : bool
    +Clear() : bool
    +IsFull() : bool
}

STM32_Memory --> RingBuffer : allocates
STM32_Memory --> SDCardBuffer : manages
ESP32_Memory --> RingBuffer : allocates

STM32_Resources ..> STM32_Memory : <color:blue><b>constrained by</b></color>
ESP32_Resources ..> ESP32_Memory : <color:blue><b>constrained by</b></color>

note top of STM32_Memory
  <b>STM32 Memory Constraints</b>
  • Limited 20KB RAM
  • Efficient buffer usage required
  • Stack overflow protection
  • Heap fragmentation prevention
end note

note top of ESP32_Memory
  <b>ESP32 Memory Advantages</b>
  • Abundant 520KB SRAM
  • FreeRTOS task stacks
  • Dynamic memory allocation
  • Multiple task contexts
end note

note bottom of RingBuffer
  <b>Ring Buffer Strategy</b>
  • ISR-safe circular buffer
  • Used by both MCUs for UART
  • Prevents data loss during bursts
  • Lock-free implementation
end note

note bottom of SDCardBuffer
  <b>SD Card Buffering</b>
  • Large persistent storage
  • Handles offline operation
  • Circular overwrite when full
  • FAT32 file system based
  • Power-loss resilient
end note

@enduml